OL,3,CElection politicking or protecting
OL,4,Cservices? Rivals row over Borders
OL,5,Cbudget
OL,7,FThe national tax and spending plans
OL,8,Fwere always going to pass because
OL,9,FLabour had indicated it would not
OL,10,Foppose them but the backing of the Lib
OL,11,FDems means the SNP doesn't even need
OL,12,Fto worry about securing its former
OL,13,Fgovernment partners in the Scottish
OL,14,FGreens.
OL,16,FAnd that means there is plenty of room
OL,17,Ffor every party to engage in more
OL,18,Fpolitical rows over your local
OL,19,Fservices and how much council tax you
OL,20,Fpay between now and May 7.
